<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 01 at 10:05AM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Scotland, Anson, Montgomery, Richmond and southeastern Stanly
Counties through 1045 AM EDT...
At 1005 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wingate, or near Monroe, moving northeast at 65 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Wadesboro, Troy, Hamlet, Biscoe, Ansonville, Hoffman,
Polkton, Norwood and Mount Gilead.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
